<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Package Management </span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Install / Remove packages:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo apt-get install &lt;pkg_name&gt; ( you add "</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">-y</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">" after "</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">apt-get</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">" to say "Yes" to all)</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo apt-get remove &lt;pkg_name&gt;</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Update/Upgrade</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo apt-get update  # To resynchronize the packages index files from their sources</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo apt-get upgrade # To install newest versions of all packages currently installed</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Search Commands:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; apt-cache search &lt;pkg_name&gt;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">even better</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; dpkg -l *&lt;pkg_name&gt;*     ( "-l" is small "L")</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Show a package description:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; apt-cache show &lt;pkg_name&gt;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; dpkg --print-avail &lt;pkg_name&gt;</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Show what files listed in the package:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; dpkg -L &lt;pkg_name&gt;</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Remove unused packages</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo apt-get auto remove -y</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span></div></en-note>